               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist (Yasay, ʾabba Yasay; on fol. 7vb, also nǝguś Yasay; sometimes only some letters of the name), of his wife (Ṭǝqmala) and of his disciples (Bälbǝyos and ʾArkayos); name of the commissioner.&#xD;
Four lines divided into 2 groups, alternating with black lines, in the incipit page of the text (fol. 3r); initial lines (2-3) of some paragraphs; the words sǝmʿu (fol. 3ra) and halleluya (fol. 29ra);&#xD;
elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
